The paper deals with crowd counting and density estimation using machine learning models, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The proposed method involves using a combination of algorithms and techniques to generate density maps, which can be considered a machine learning task and thus falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the limitations of existing benchmark datasets, which can be considered a critique of current research and thus falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper addresses the issue of safety and security applications, which can be considered a concern for cybersecurity (cs.CR) sub-category.
